WEBVTT

00:10:57.655 --> 00:11:00.663
You know, it's tempting, perhaps,

00:11:00.687 --> 00:11:04.433
to focus on the prejudiced attitudes

00:11:04.457 --> 00:11:07.894
of the men and the workers
that I heard in Mississippi.

00:11:07.918 --> 00:11:10.587
But I'm more interested
in holding accountable

00:11:10.611 --> 00:11:14.497
the people who are selling
racist ideas for their profit

00:11:14.521 --> 00:11:17.397
than those who are desperate
enough to buy it.

00:11:19.351 --> 00:11:21.200
My travels also took me to places

00:11:21.224 --> 00:11:24.914
where I saw, however,
that it doesn't have to be this way.

00:11:24.938 --> 00:11:27.834
I went to Maine,
the whitest state in the nation,

00:11:27.858 --> 00:11:29.342
the oldest,

00:11:29.366 --> 00:11:31.941
where there are more deaths
every year than births,